jobInfo.postDescription:
Apifox is a widely popular API development collaboration tool, and we strive to provide developers with an ultimate development experience. As of 2022, the total market value of the API R&D ecosystem has exceeded 10 billion USD. The management team of Apifox is composed of senior engineers from Tencent. You will work alongside a group of energetic, straightforward, and outstanding engineers to promote the "API-ization" globally and domestically.

Our office is located in the Tianhe CBD, with convenient transportation and environment. By joining Apifox, you will receive stock options and bonuses that match your potential, and upon joining, you will be equipped with a MacBook Pro and a 4K monitor.

Before applying, we hope you understand us:
1. We are a Geek team, only recruiting excellent technical talents (those with strong capabilities or those who are currently average but love learning and can grow quickly);
2. We focus on the technical atmosphere of the team, emphasizing the learning and growth of technical personnel, with weekly technical learning and sharing sessions, Code Reviews;
3. We focus on code quality, and substandard code is unacceptable;
4. If you are not someone who loves learning and tinkering, please do not apply, as you will not be able to integrate into the team even if you join;
5. We believe that excellent people only want to work with excellent people;
6. We have flat management, without the intrigue of the workplace, without rules and regulations, we believe that excellent technical people do not need to be managed;
7. Come here, let the excellent you, only work with excellent people.

Responsibilities include:
- Participating in the testing work of the project iteration within the project group and the entire R&D process quality control, tracking production issues, etc.
- Participating in the software testing project work of the Apifox project;
- Participating in test planning, test requirement analysis, test case design, writing test scripts, test execution, test reporting, and other testing activities;
- Communicating fully with team members, coordinating with the demand side and development side in a timely manner for issues encountered in the testing project to ensure the progress and quality of testing;
- Defect analysis and summary, test project summary, organizing test documents, training, and knowledge sharing;
- Adhering to the test process system, strictly following the specifications for the test process and test deliverables;
- Deployment and maintenance of the test environment;
- Other daily work in the project.

We are looking for someone like you:
1. Bachelor's degree or above, major in computer-related fields;
2. Familiar with the software testing process, mastering software testing analysis methodology and testing techniques, with experience in interface testing, automated testing;
3. Familiar with tools such as Jmeter, Postman, proficient in using svn, git, ZenTao;
4. Have good learning ability and problem analysis ability, able to have a clear analysis of complex logic;
5. Have experience and ability in writing test plans, test schemes, and test reports;
6. Priority will be given to those with study or work experience in English-speaking countries.

We hope you are:
1. Identify with our philosophy: pursuing efficiency, promoting automation, and a culture of continuous improvement.
2. Have a code obsession and engineering mindset: we expect you to be a value-creating engineer, not a labor-selling programmer.
3. Have a Geek style: identify with the UNIX design philosophy, proficient in using various Geek tools.
4. Be good at collaboration and communication: have a foundation in team communication, collaboration, project progress, and time management.
5. Be a lifelong learner: keep learning, love sharing, have a broad technical vision, and be sensitive to new technologies in the industry.
